Kokborok:
Hakhe Musi bai Israilsarok, Subraiyungni thani
o rwchapmungno rwchap lai kha;
“Ang Subraiyungni thani rwchapnai,
tamni hwn ba bo chẃngsacha khe kwplai wng kha;
bo korairokno tei korai kanairokno twijlango khiklaiwi rw kha.

English:
Then Moses and the people of Israel sang this song to the Lord, saying,
“I will sing to the Lord, for he has triumphed gloriously;
the horse and his rider he has thrown into the sea.

Kokborok:
Nini bukungni hama bai khe twirok
kuchugo rúngjagwi thumjago,
twi kotor kuchugo khe thumjak kha;
twijlang bokhrini twirok raksaui ma thángo;

English:
At the blast of thy nostrils the waters piled up,
the floods stood up in a heap;
the deeps congealed in the heart of the sea.

Kokborok:
“Nwng kók narwgwi swmai rwma tẃi khe bórokno
tẃither kha, nwng phiyókma borokno tẃither kha;
nini phan bai khe tolwi nini ha kwtharo lama soui bórokno tlang kha.

Idomni tẃiphangrok mok lai kha,
Moabni tẃiphangrok kiriui kwlwibrajak;
bebak Kanano tongnairok bwkha báijak bái kha.

English:
Now are the chiefs of Edom dismayed;
the leaders of Moab, trembling seizes them;
all the inhabitants of Canaan have melted away.

And Miriam sang to them:
“Sing to the Lord, for he has triumphed gloriously;
the horse and his rider he has thrown into the sea.”

Kokborok:
Lamek bihiksongno hai hwnwi sa kha:
“Ada bai Jilla norok khna di;
ano swprakma bai ang sikla khoroksano buthar kha.

Bo hai hwnwibo sa kha,
“Sem ani Subraiyung Kaitor bai hamcha rwjak thung;
tei Kanan khe bini seleng ma wng thung.

English:
He also said,
“Blessed by the Lord my God be Shem;
and let Canaan be his slave.

Kokborok:
Kaitor Japhetno hamcha rw thung,
tei bo Semni nogo ma tong thung;
tei Kanan Japhetni seleng ma wngnai.”

English:
God enlarge Japheth,
and let him dwell in the tents of Shem;
and let Canaan be his slave.”

And he blessed him and said,
“Blessed be Abram by God Most High,
maker of heaven and earth;

the angel who has redeemed me from all evil, bless the lads;
and in them let my name be perpetuated, and the name of my fathers Abraham and Isaac;
and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.”

Unstable as water, you shall not have pre-eminence
because you went up to your father's bed;
then you defiled it—you went up to my couch!

Kokborok:
O ani bwkha, bórokni kókbiti sa laima-o ta phai di;
ani phola bórok bai pal ta gwdal di;
tamni hwn khe bórok thamchi tungjagwi
borokrokno butharo tei bórok thwng laina bagwi musuk
chwlarokni yastwngni sirduk rasu lai-o.

English:
O my soul, come not into their council;
O my spirit, be not joined to their company;
for in their anger they slay men,
and in their wantonness they hamstring oxen.

Kokborok:
“Juda, nini takhuksong nono lobnai;
nwng nini kebengnai arirokno gwdna-o romnai;
nwphani bwsarok nono bomwi khulumnai.

English:
Judah, your brothers shall praise you;
your hand shall be on the neck of your enemies;
your father's sons shall bow down before you.

Kokborok:
“Jebulun khe twijlang rukungo tongnai;
bini aro rungtorrokni bathakthai kaham kuk wngnai,
bini ha ari Sidon jora wngnai.

English:
Zebulun shall dwell at the shore of the sea;
he shall become a haven for ships,
and his border shall be at Sidon.

Joseph is a fruitful bough,
a fruitful bough by a spring;
his branches run over the wall.

Kokborok:
Nini nwphani aroni hamari abo ang swkango apha
chuchusongni aro manmani hamarini slái’-bo ham kugo;
abo kusung kusung tongnai hathái jora thángwi sógwi kha;
abo Josepni bokhorok saka o klai si thung,
bini takhuksong bai swkakjaknaini bokhorokni thani klai thung.
